About
We offer free customer pick-up and drop-off in a genuine US military HMMWV (Humvee) Also, we have a collection of over 600 machineguns from around the world at our 5-acre facility. You can shoot .50 Caliber Barrett sniper rifles, grenade launchers, .50 M2HB Brownings or even classic WWII Lugers, 1911's, STG-44/MP-44's, M1 Garands or even MG-42'. From the trenches of World War I all the way to the current conflict in Afghanistan, we have the weapon systems in our inventory. The property also has a military Huey UH-1C helicopter, M4A3 Sherman, "M1 Abrams" main battle tank, CH-34 "Choctaw" helicopter, FV432 armored personnel carrier, M2A1 Halftrack, Army trucks, Humvee's and various jeeps and other military vehicles for the experience!

BigErn05
Wellington11 contributions
Awesome experience we can't get back home that left us with an adrenalin rush. Highly recommended.
Oct 2024 • Friends
Myself and 6 other friends from New Zealand visited Battlefield Vegas in late Oct 2024. All of us are not familiar with weapons, in fact I was the only one with a firearms license (back in the day) and previous experience shooting (.22, 308s and shot guns and my experience in doing this was very limited). This context made us uncertain to some extent about what Battlefield Vegas would be like.

In the end, all of us thought the experience was amazing and it was better than what we thought it would be. The experience left some or possibly all of us with a natural adrenalin rush that kept on going for at least 2 or 3 hours. We were like excited school boys after we left as we compared our experiences and reviewed photos/videos and hours later we were still talking about it. For some of us it was a Top 3 Highlight from our busy week in Vegas. I think we also all got a new found respect for the power that weapons like this have and are happy they are not in proliferation back home.

On the subject of cost, it isn't cheap (especially considering we earn $NZ) but we all walked away smiling and feeling we got value for money and we didn't care about the cost. This sense of value for money came from the rush of it but also from the fact that this is simply an experience we could never get back home. This was unique for us.

I fired a M1 Garand, an M14, a K98 Mauser, a Lee Enfield No.3 and the Bren gun and was hugely satisfied with what I choose.

BTW, the staff we dealt with were all professional, helpful and friendly but in a no mucking around sort of way, which is what you want when dealing with weapons.

Highly recommend this experience and I know if I am back to Vegas, I'll be back to give it another go.
Written November 4, 2024
